					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-10815154#post-4199176</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-10815154/scp-4233#post-4199176</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Thu, 28 Mar 2019 01:06:29 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>OthellotheCat</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>3213383</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Alright, as one of the two people to have downvoted this, I feel as though I should explain why I did so.</p> <p>This is well-written, but I feel like that encouraging a family of X Champions would be like encouraging a slew of dado skips. Some of them may be good, but some of them may just boil down the character to their base elements in hopes of getting upvotes. It's a similar reason why people are iffy about GAW, dado and WWS; they're good when done right, but they're easy enough to write for on the surface that it ends up being a new writer's trap.</p> <p>While I love GAW, dado and WWS, Moon Champion deserved to be a one-off, and I don't think it warranted a sequel. I've since rescinded my downvote to a no-vote, but I really hope that it stays at a family of two.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
